reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best overall Sonicare toothbrush
reviews.reviewText: This is the best electric toothbrush within the Sonicare range of power brushes.It offers a great balance of features and performance for the price and is a great buy.The water resistant handle is slim, light and feels quite grippy despite the lack of textured surfaces on the handle.2 intensity settings are available. This gives you a high and low option depending how powerful you want the cleaning to be.The 4100 offers 31,000 bristle movements per minute which is less than its predecessor at 62,000. But the motor has been configured that despite offering half the bristle movements, the cleaning sensation and results are comparable. I struggle to tell the difference. The clean is invigorating and my teeth felt great after each use.The BrushSync technology that tracks the brush head and activates the light on the handle is clever. It does mean the brush heads are a bit more expensive. You don't need this feature, but it is handy if your are not very good at remembering to replace the heads regularly.There is a 2 minute timer, pacer and pressure sensor, all work well. The vibration of the pressure sensor in the handle is really obvious, so you can take corrective action quickly.The battery life is said to be 2 weeks, I achieved a little over that at 17 days on the high intensity setting.There is a new charging stand included. It has a USB connector at the end of the cable rather than a 2 pin power adapter. It is potentially more convenient for some but if you do want to charge from a wall socket, you need to source your own USB to 2 pin adapter.Pros+ 2 intensity settings – choose between low and high power+ The timer and pacer encourage brushing for the recommended time+ Slim handle design – stylish & easy to keep clean+ USB charging stand makes it more convenient for some+ BrushSync technology – reminder when brush heads need replacingCons- Fewer bristle movements than most other Sonicare brushes- The pressure sensor isn’t visible – vibrates the handle instead- No indicator lights to show which intensity is selected- USB charger makes it less convenient for some- Battery life isn’t as good as some other Sonicare brushes

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The first ten days of using this toothbrush handset I hated it. I charged it for 4 hours and started using it. It was weak and the battery didn’t seem to hold charge. I almost sent it back.Then I RTFM (read the instruction manual). First, you need to charge a full 24 hours the first time. Second, there is a “ get acquainted mode” that is automatically employed in the first several uses that significantly limits the speed. This mode is automatically turned off after several uses but can be turned off manually. Third, there are two speeds, “Barely adequate “ and “Decently strong“. First press starts at barely adequate, then second press changes to “that’s what I wanted”.I am now quite happy with this handset. And the battery life is quite good, adequate for weekend travel without the charger adapter (USB-A adapter provided, BYO charger).

reviews.reviewText: So, got my hands on the Philips Sonicare 4100 via Slickdeals.⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Here's the rundown:Love the toothbrush, but surprise – no brick charger included. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Game-Changer for Dental Health
reviews.reviewText: The PHILIPS Sonicare 4100 Power Toothbrush has completely transformed my dental care routine, and I couldn't be more thrilled with the results! This rechargeable electric toothbrush has taken my oral hygiene to a whole new level, leaving my teeth feeling remarkably clean and my dentist impressed with the improvements.Right from the start, the toothbrush's design impressed me. The slim, ergonomic handle fits perfectly in my hand, making it comfortable to hold and easy to maneuver during brushing. It's evident that PHILIPS prioritizes user experience in their product design.The sonic technology used in the brush head is where the real magic happens. The high-frequency vibrations gently but effectively remove plaque and stains, ensuring a thorough cleaning that is far superior to manual brushing. With the two-minute timer and quad-pacer feature, I can be confident that I'm brushing each quadrant of my mouth for the optimal duration.The brushing modes add versatility to the Sonicare 4100, allowing me to choose between Clean, White, and Gum Care modes depending on my needs. This customizable approach ensures my dental care is tailored to my specific oral health requirements.One of the standout features of this electric toothbrush is its long-lasting battery life. After a full charge, it lasts for weeks before needing to be recharged, making it an excellent companion for travel or for those who prefer not to worry about frequent charging.The included ProResults brush head is gentle on my gums yet tough on plaque, and it's easily replaceable when needed. Additionally, the brush head reminder helps me keep track of when it's time for a replacement, ensuring I maintain optimal dental care.I've noticed a significant improvement in my overall dental health since using the PHILIPS Sonicare 4100 Power Toothbrush. My teeth feel cleaner, look whiter, and my gums are healthier than ever before. Even my dental hygienist noticed the difference during my last check-up!Cleaning the toothbrush is a breeze, and I appreciate the convenient travel case that keeps it protected when I'm on the go.In conclusion, the PHILIPS Sonicare 4100 Power Toothbrush has surpassed my expectations in every aspect. Its powerful performance, user-friendly design, and customizable features have made it an indispensable part of my dental care routine. I highly recommend the PHILIPS Sonicare 4100 to anyone seeking an efficient and effective solution for maintaining excellent oral health. Thank you, Amazon, for offering such a remarkable product that has truly made a positive impact on my dental care journey.
